  "server": {
    "name": "io.nyc.bic",
    "title": "NYC Business Integrity Commission (BIC)",
    "version": "0.1.0",
    "description": "Agent-native access to the New York City Business Integrity Commission \u2014 trade waste hauler licensees, broker/self-hauler/construction-and-demolition registrants, public wholesale-market businesses (Hunts Point, Fulton Fish), the licensee/registrant vehicle fleet, issued violations, and complaints from NYC Open Data, plus the net-new ability to apply for and track a trade waste license/registration that today lives only in the Salesforce Experience Cloud portal.",
    "instructions": "Use find_licensees / get_licensee to locate trade waste hauler licensees by borough, council district, or free text, and find_registrants for broker, self-hauler, and construction-and-demolition registrations. find_market_businesses covers the public wholesale markets. find_vehicles (and get_licensee_vehicles) returns BIC-plated hauler fleet detail including side-guard compliance. find_violations and find_complaints answer enforcement and integrity questions about a given BIC NUMBER. apply_for_license (net-new) submits a trade waste license/registration/exemption application; it requires an authenticated applicant and mutates state \u2014 confirm the industry, application type, and applicant identity with the user before submitting. All registry results are point-in-time Open Data snapshots (see EXPORT DATE)."
  },
